<div id="review_4048941730" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4048941730" />
    <a title="Meg loves to read" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9739976-meg-loves-to-read"><img alt="Meg loves to read" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615526545p2/9739976.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4048941730?book_show_action=true">Jun 22, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Meg loves to read" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Meg loves to read" href="/user/show/9739976-meg-loves-to-read">Meg loves to read</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4048941730" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1586530955159809399">“We’re doing it because we’re in the pack, because we’re afraid not to be in the pack. We don’t dare show our pack weakness; we don’t dare resist the pack.”<br/><br/>This book was written in 1940, during a time of great animosity and turbulence in the world. Hitler was at his height of power and the world was changing in a way that we can never forget. And it was during this time that Mr. Clark challenged the idea of anarchy rising against anarchy and the consequences that follow. He challenged that a naz</span>
  <span id="freeText1586530955159809399" style="display:none">“We’re doing it because we’re in the pack, because we’re afraid not to be in the pack. We don’t dare show our pack weakness; we don’t dare resist the pack.”<br /><br />This book was written in 1940, during a time of great animosity and turbulence in the world. Hitler was at his height of power and the world was changing in a way that we can never forget. And it was during this time that Mr. Clark challenged the idea of anarchy rising against anarchy and the consequences that follow. He challenged that a nazi Germany could happen anywhere - even in our own backyard. <br /><br />The book happens in just a 24 hour period, but I found bits of the book to be a bit slow (a lot of talking). There are some racial slurs too, that bring down the overall experience. However, this classic westerner is worth the read, because it challenges the ugly sides of pack humanity.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1586530955159809399" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


