<div id="review_830343186" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/830343186" />
    <a title="Sandy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5599813-sandy"><img alt="Sandy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1390332466p2/5599813.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/830343186?book_show_action=true">Jan 21, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sandy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sandy" href="/user/show/5599813-sandy">Sandy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5599813-sandy?shelf=read-2014">read-2014</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer830343186" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2192110111224862196">In this classic western published in 1940 and made into the iconic movie starring Henry Fonda in 1943, in 1885, two cowpokes come into the dying town of Bridger&apos;s Wells following the spring round-up. While there drinking whisky, fighting, playing poker, and hearing the latest gossip (there have been cattle rustlers in the area hitting most of the herds), a young man comes racing into town with the terrible that ranch hand Larry Kinkaid has been murdered out on the range, shot through the head. H</span>
  <span id="freeText2192110111224862196" style="display:none">In this classic western published in 1940 and made into the iconic movie starring Henry Fonda in 1943, in 1885, two cowpokes come into the dying town of Bridger's Wells following the spring round-up. While there drinking whisky, fighting, playing poker, and hearing the latest gossip (there have been cattle rustlers in the area hitting most of the herds), a young man comes racing into town with the terrible that ranch hand Larry Kinkaid has been murdered out on the range, shot through the head. His buddy, Jeff Farnley, immediately wants to go after the rustlers that killed his pal. While a couple of the townsfolk try to talk him down with the advice that the sheriff should handle it, others decide that justice is too slow, and the rustlers/murderers need to be run down and strung up. Then former Confederate Major Tetley takes the lead, there's no turning back, and the 'posse' go after three men seen herding cattle bearing the brand of the ranch where the murder takes place.<br /><br />While I'm glad I read the book because of it's classic designation, if I have to be honest, I didn't love it. The build up was terribly slow, and frankly I'm just not sure how the heat to track these men down and kill them was maintained, at least not based on the pace of the book. Certainly the scenes where they find their quarry and proceed with their plan to lynch them without trial (except for the 'trial' conducted by Tetley) is chilling, again there is a long delay that seems would have caused some of the men to cool off. But I guess the point was that one man with a firm grip on the others will lead good men into bad deeds, deeds they will have to live with for the rest of their lives because shortly after the deed is done, they learn they've just hanged three innocent men.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2192110111224862196" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


