<div id="review_2029260945" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2029260945" />
    <a title="Vicki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/142188-vicki"><img alt="Vicki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1182391069p2/142188.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2029260945?book_show_action=true">Jun 17, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vicki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vicki" href="/user/show/142188-vicki">Vicki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/142188-vicki?shelf=library-books">library-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/142188-vicki?shelf=novels">novels</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/142188-vicki?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/142188-vicki?shelf=the-american-west">the-american-west</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2029260945" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6533701844458522147">Two restless and edgy cowboys come off the winter range and into town for the first time in months ... only to find that the only single woman for miles has decamped for the city, cattle have been going missing from nearby ranches, and now a man has been murdered. Joining the posse to catch the rustler/murderer(s?) is the only way to keep suspicion from falling on them.<br/><br/>This is a really nuanced look at violence, fairness, justice, and performative masculinity. The writing is thoughtful but straig</span>
  <span id="freeText6533701844458522147" style="display:none">Two restless and edgy cowboys come off the winter range and into town for the first time in months ... only to find that the only single woman for miles has decamped for the city, cattle have been going missing from nearby ranches, and now a man has been murdered. Joining the posse to catch the rustler/murderer(s?) is the only way to keep suspicion from falling on them.<br /><br />This is a really nuanced look at violence, fairness, justice, and performative masculinity. The writing is thoughtful but straightforward, and the setting was beautiful and evocative. Didn't know what I was in for when I started, but great read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6533701844458522147" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


